race.comment: MR CONSPIRACY (5) finished out of the money when fresh from a spell two starts back then he was never in contention when tenth over 1800m at Hawkesbury. Has the class to take care of this field. FARRAIGE (11) is a thirty-seven-start maiden who finished seventh at his most recent appearance over 2100m at Gosford. Looks to be in the right race to play a big role today. NAPOLI (10) has not won for a long while. Chipped away late when fourth over 1600m at Dubbo. Going up a level this time but has the ability to mix it with them. EVER WAS (3) comes through a similar race at Goulburn last time out and jumps straight to 2000m now. Third-up into the campaign, he still has improvement to come and he can play a major role.
